# Persist rendered test file as a content-hashed TestArtifact — Architecture doc Section 7.1
#
# Trigger: ReactRenderer/render is the concrete renderer concept introduced in MAG-907
# (repertoire/concepts/test-plan-renderers/react-renderer.concept). When additional renderer
# concepts land (PlaywrightRenderer, etc.) a corresponding sync should be added for each, or
# this sync generalised if the sync grammar gains disjunctive when-clauses.
#
# Where-clause joins: ReactRenderer/render returns ok(code: String) — it does not carry
# specKind, sourceRef, or platform in its completion output. These fields are obtained by
# joining through TestPlan state (planId -> specKind, invariantId) and InvariantParser state
# (invariantId -> sourceRef). The `platform` is fixed to "react" for this renderer — a
# generalised version would bind it from PluginRegistry once all renderers share a common
# render interface carrying the platform name out in their completion.
#
# TODO: once TestPlanRenderer interface is formalised in MAG-907 and all renderers emit
# `platform` + `specKind` + `sourceRef` in their ok completion, this sync's where-clause
# can be simplified to drop the state joins. Track as a follow-up to MAG-907.
#
# outputPath derivation: TestArtifact/write determines the final file path from its inputs.
# Inline path derivation (e.g., concat("generated/tests/", ?src)) is left as a TODO — Clef's
# sync grammar supports concat() expressions in field assignments but the exact output path
# convention is established by TestArtifact's handler, not by this sync.

sync WriteArtifactOnRender [eager]
  purpose {
    After ReactRenderer/render produces test code, persist it as a TestArtifact using
    content-hashing so regeneration is a diff, not a blind overwrite.
  }
when {
  ReactRenderer/render: [ plan: ?planId ]
    => ok(code: ?code)
}
where {
  TestPlan: { ?planId specKind: ?k; invariantId: ?inv }
  InvariantParser: { ?inv sourceRef: ?src }
}
then {
  TestArtifact/write: [
    specKind: ?k;
    sourceRef: ?src;
    platform: "react";
    outputPath: concat("generated/tests/", ?src, ".react.test.ts");
    content: ?code
  ]
}
